Venezuela’s Chavez Proposes ‘State Council’ to Make Policy

-- B y   C o r i n a   R o d r i g u e z   P o n s   a n d   J o s e   O r o z c o
-- 
2011-08-06T23:02:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-06/venezuela-s-chavez-proposes-state-council-to-make-policy.html
Venezuelan President  Hugo Chavez ,
speaking on state television, proposed the creation of a “state
council,” led by the vice president and five ministers, that
would propose laws and policies to solve the country’s problems.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Corina Rodriguez Pons in Caracas at 
